---

## ğŸš€ Tech Stack

### Frontend
- Next.js 15
- React 19
- TailwindCSS
- Axios
- Socket.io Client
- React Hot Toast
- Moment.js

### Backend
- Node.js + TypeScript
- Nodemon
- Concurrently (dev mode)
- Compiled output â†’ `dist/`

---

## ğŸ§© Frontend â€” Scripts

Path: `frontend/package.json`

| Command | Description |
|--------|-----------|
| `npm run dev` | Start Next.js dev server |
| `npm run build` | Build production bundle |
| `npm run start` | Start production build |
| `npm run lint` | Run Next.js lint |

Run frontend dev server:

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

---

## ğŸ§© Backend â€” Scripts

Path: `backend/package.json`

| Command | Description |
|--------|-----------|
| `npm run dev` | Watch + auto-restart (tsc + nodemon) |
| `npm run build` | Compile TypeScript to `dist/` |
| `npm run start` | Run compiled server |

Run backend in dev mode:

```bash
cd backend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Build backend for production:

```bash
npm run build
npm run start
```

> The server runs from: `dist/index.js`

---

## âš™ï¸ Environment Variables

Create `.env` files:

```
frontend/.env.local
backend/.env
```

Add your keys such as:

```
DATABASE_URL=
JWT_SECRET=
API_BASE_URL=
SOCKET_SERVER_URL=
```

(Adjust based on your project)

